  "body": "## Description\r\nI'm new to TypeScript and Buidler, so I'm sorry if this is a false positive. While reading Rahul's [article](https://hackernoon.com/the-new-solidity-dev-stack-buidler-ethers-waffle-typescript-706830w0), I got stuck at this:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nimport { ethers } from \"@nomiclabs/buidler\";\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt doesn't work - \"ethers\" cannot be found in builder's dist file. I checked the [buidler.dev docs](https://buidler.dev/guides/waffle-testing.html) and you're indicating to use the same \"ethers\" object (the import is in CommonJS form, but it doesn't matter).\r\n\r\n## Screen Capture\r\n\r\n<img width=\"922\" alt=\"Capture d’écran 2020-05-20 à 03 24 35\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8782666/82391683-95d14a00-9a4a-11ea-974a-564a0814f648.png\">",
